The paper discusses machine learning models and their biases, which suggests it belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also mentions image reconstruction and change detection, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep latent variable models and information bottleneck theory suggests it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The evaluation of the model on biological sex prediction suggests it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) category. Finally, the use of VAEs and deep learning suggests it may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) category.
